etrization, we get $z_t=0.66^{+0.03}_{-0.04}$, $\\tau=0.33^{+0.04}_{-0.04}$\nand $q_0=-0.54^{+0.05}_{-0.07}$, in excellent agreement with flat $\\Lambda$CDM\nfor which $\\tau=1/3$. We also obtain for flat wCDM, another dark energy model\ndescribed by our parametrization, the constraint on the equation of state\nparameter -1.22 < w < -0.78 at more than 99% confidence level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 May 2015 17:48:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Feb 2016 16:32:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-01"}
